{
  "texts": [
    "Electron microscopy (EM):",
    "technique that uses electron beams instead of visible light to achieve much higher resolution in imaging (Hayes and Pease, 1968).",
    "Epileptogenic zone: macroscopic/microscopic brain lesion responsible for the generation of seizures (Jehi, 2018).",
    "Fast Marching Method (FMM): numerical method for finding the global minimum of an energy function (Sethian, 1996).",
    "Fields Of View (FOV): in optical instruments is the angle at the camera's vertex, created by the two edges that represent the maximum range within which the measured target's object can traverse (Gao S. et al., 2022)."
  ]
}